study_area: Papua New Guinea, Ilahita area of Maprik district, East Sepik Province
study_title: Differential impact of malaria control interventions on P.falciparum and P.vivax infections in young Papua New Guinean children
incidence_definition: (history) of febrile illness 48h, LM detected, any density
prevalence_PCR_diagnostic_method: qPCR (in 2nd and 3rd surevy), in first survey: semi quantitative post-PCR ligase detection reaction/fluorescent microscpehere assay
comments_prevalence: sample size is the number of children in the cohort
Intervention1: LLIN 1st round
Intervention2: LLIN 2nd round
implementation_dates_exact_comment: exact at least for the LLIN, also for second round LLIN from graph
baselin_intervention: nothing
standard_of_care: AL or amodiaquine and SP, no primaquine, switch to AL and also primaquine in beginning of 2012, also then test and treat approach
cluster_trial_concern: yes, different villages
cluster_trial_addressed: no, take into account clustering of repeated measurements in childred

study_title: The epidemiology of Plasmodium falciparum and Plasmodium vivax in East Sepik Province, Papua New Guinea, pre- and post-implementation of national malaria control efforts
Intervention1: LLIN 1st dist
Intervention2: LLIN 2nd dist
implementation_dates_exact_comment: N, LLIN 1st round in 2008, test and treat end of 2011 beginning of 2012
baselin_intervention: no spraying mentioned, had nets before. Coverage around 88% but most likely untreated nets
standard_of_care: before switch (according to omekaius): AL or amodiaquine and SP, end 2011 beginnning of 2012 switch to AL as first line and primaquine for vivax: for 14 days 0.25mg/kg
cluster_trial_concern: no, seperate data for villages
cluster_trial_addressed: not necessary

study_title: Reduction in incidence and prevalence of Plasmodium falciparum in under-5-year-old children by permethrin impregnation of mosquito nets
Intervention1: treatment (chloroquine and sulfadoxine/pyrimethamine) (first time)
Intervention2: permethrin-impregnated nets (many owned nets before, not sure when and how they got them)
coverage2: high, 98.6 reported using net in final survey
implementation_dates_exact_comment: they are exact because it is an RCT so we know the time difference between measurement and implementation
baselin_intervention: many children already had a net before, nothing else mentioned
standard_of_care: probably chloroquine (villages have village aid that give this as presumptive treatment)
transmission: in table 7, for Pf: before all below 1,  as well for vivax
cluster_trial_concern: yes, i think although give data for villages seperately, but i aggregated data for bigger sample size
cluster_trial_addressed: not necessary
study_type: trial but control group with untreated nets

study_title: Repeated mosquito net distributions, improved treatment, and trends in malaria cases in sentinel health facilities in Papua New Guinea
incidence_definition: (history of) fever in patients that visit SHF and RDT positive
incidence_diagnostics: RDT positive and then species determination with LM
unit_incidence_rate: number of 100 fever cases caused by malaria species
comments_incidence: web plot digitizer,not actual incidence rate!!some have 'no species data available' but very few, so not a big issue
Intervention1: LLIN 3rd round
coverage1: self reported use after distribution:69% in 2013 and 48% in 2014
implementation_dates_exact_comment: yes gives exact month
baselin_intervention: 2nd distribution of nets 2 months before they started surveillance in 2011
standard_of_care: amodiaquine or cloroquine plus SP, switch(august2012) to ACT (AL) and primaquine with Pvivax (not 'consistently' done though)
cluster_trial_concern: no because already sentonel sites taken seperately
cluster_trial_addressed: not necessary

study_title: Entomological and epidemiological attributes for malaria transmission and implementation of vector control in southern Iran
incidence_definition: no definition, is cases that were reported
sample_size_incidence_number_people: 31292 (population in district in 2009)
Intervention1: LLIN (seemed to hae nets before and distributed them, not sure how extensivelxy)
implementation_dates_exact_comment: just says which year
baselin_intervention: IRS (lambdacyhalothrin in 03 (and i guess 2002?), deltamethrin from 2004 up until 2007, twice: march and august, not sure if there was spraying before 2002 too),some larviciding in 2007 as well, says as well there was some net distribution
standard_of_care: Pf: chloroquine in 2004 switch to chloroquine plus sulfadoxine-pyrimethamine, in 2009 to artesunate plus sulfadoxine-pyrimethamine, Pv: chloroquine and primaquine weekly for eight weeks (page 45 of 'history of the successful struggle against malaria in the islamic republic of iran')
cluster_trial_concern: yes because is from a whole district
cluster_trial_addressed: no, or not mentioned

cluster_trial_concern: yes because is from a whole district
cluster_trial_addressed: no, or not mentioned

study_title: Malaria epidemiology in Lihir Island, Papua New Guinea
incidence_definition: Fever above 37.5 (or withing last 48h) and confirmed by LM

standard_of_care: since 2005: AS and SP, in 2009: AL
cluster_trial_concern: yes, because different villages in the catchment area
cluster_trial_addressed: no, dont think they adjusted for this, sued robust SE for things like age and year though

study_title: Impact of DDT spraying on malaria transmission in Bareilly District, Uttar Pradesh, India
Intervention1: DDT spraying two rounds one aug/sep the second nov/dec, dont know if any spraying happened the year before, if it did, then not mentioned, but 'control' villages were also sprayed by state health authorities, so could have happened before)
coverage1: 95.3% of houses sprayed and second round 87%
baselin_intervention: none found
standard_of_care: in study treated with chloroquine when ill at collection (so assume not chloroquine resitant area), Pf: CQ and PQ one dose, Pv: CQ and 5 days PQ (according to Anvikar et al.)
cluster_trial_concern: yes, used six villages but call it cluster of village? So maybe similar
cluster_trial_addressed: no, or not mentioned

study_title: Characterization of Plasmodium falciparum and Plasmodium vivax recent exposure in an area of significantly decreased transmission intensity in Central Vietnam
incidence_definition: cases from routine monthly reports of commune health centers
sample_size_incidence_number_people: missing
Intervention1: IRS (nov 13, apr 14, april 15, august 15) not clear if there was sprayin before or not)
Intervention2: LLIN (not known which round)
coverage2: missing but in one commune had high coverage with only 2.5% of households no nets
implementation_dates_exact_comment: yes month given in discussion
baselin_intervention: not sure, does not really mention anything aboiut what happened before, but as it is elimination stage they porbably had things before.
standard_of_care: missing (couldn't really find clear source for that time Thanh2017 has guidlines from 2009 where they used 3 day DP for Pf, for Pv since 2009 CQ and 14 days primaquine (thanh2015) not sure if any changes between then and study)
cluster_trial_concern: yes, there are several villages in the commune
cluster_trial_addressed: no, or not mentioned

sample_size_incidence_number_people: missing, say something abot how many people in subdiustrict but dont know what that means

baselin_intervention: none
standard_of_care: doesnt say but talk about restiance chloroquine and sulfadoxine and pyrimethamine so maybe use those
cluster_trial_concern: yes, i think there are districts and they have several aid posts

study_area: Brazil, Rondonia, costa Margue + Forte principe de beira + settlement along BR429
study_title: Effects of immigration on the prevalence of malaria in rural areas of the amazon basin of brazil
incidence_definition: positive blood slide at SUCAM clinic
sample_size_incidence_number_people: no exact numbers: in 86/87 around 3600 people, a lot of migration, porbably had less people before that
comments_incidence: web plot digitizer, underestimated as it is the data from clinic and don't know how many seek treatment
Intervention1: MDA (might be first time, doesn't really say anything, doesn't say what drug used)
baselin_intervention: spraying with DDT
standard_of_care: missing, but speak about experiences with chloroquine for vivax and falciparum treatment and also fansidar (sulfadoxin and pyrimethamine)
cluster_trial_concern: no because only one clinic
cluster_trial_addressed: not necessary

sample_size_incidence_number_people: no exact numbers: in 86/87 around 3600 people, a lot of migration, porbably had less people before that
comments_incidence: web plot digitizer, underestimated as it is the data from clinic and don't know how many seek treatment
Intervention1: MDA (might be first time, doesn't really say anything, doesn't say what drug used)
baselin_intervention: spraying with DDT
standard_of_care: missing, but speak about experiences with chloroquine for vivax and falciparum treatment and also fansidar (sulfadoxin and pyrimethamine)
cluster_trial_concern: no because only one clinic
cluster_trial_addressed: not necessary

study_title: Analysis of trend of malaria prevalence in south-west Ethiopia: a retrospective comparative study
incidence_definition: cases reported at local primary health care units
sample_size_incidence_number_people: around 50000 residents
comments_incidence: web plot digitizer, have a lake there because of dam
Intervention1: increased case management: health posts with health extension workers, village level
Intervention2: LLIN distribution (first)
baselin_intervention: did IRS with a change in 2010 to deltamethrin or bendiocarb
standard_of_care: Pv: Chloroquine, Pf: SP and in 2004 shift to AL
transmission: estimats from figure 3: indec 203 quick peak at below 2 then below 1 and a peak below 3 in dec 2008 and peak below 4 in dec 2009. but is for both species
cluster_trial_concern: yes, several villages
cluster_trial_addressed: no or not mentioned

study_title: The complex relationship of exposure to new Plasmodium infections and incidence of clinical malaria Papua New Guinea
pr_what_done_mixed: doesn't say (assume counted towards both Pv and Pf)
comments_prevalence: web plot digitizer
Intervention1: AL(over 3 days) and CQ (over 3 days 25mg/kg total dose) and placebo (no mention of it being done before)
coverage1: all of the children that were followed completed treatment (but other people in village were not covered)
implementation_dates_exact_comment: pretty much, not exact exact but kinda around this time. Month is at least correct
baselin_intervention: pretty high coverage of LLIN
standard_of_care: accoriding to ome-kaius in 2008 which is around that time: AL or amodiaquine and sulphadoxine-pyrimethamine. Primaquine not adapted (according to betuela2012 only formally done in 2010)
cluster_trial_concern: yes, is in several villages
cluster_trial_addressed: not sure, used GEE but not sure if only to account for repeated measure in individual, but dont have CI for prevalence anyway
study_type: trial: no control though because compared one regimen with primaquine and one without

study_title: The impact of artemisinin combination therapy and long-lasting insecticidal nets on forest malaria incidence in tribal villages of india, 2006-2011
incidence_definition: active and passive case detection, confirmed with slide, history of fever or fever for active case detection
mixed_what_done: not sure, not seperate, probably counted towards falciparum, but only few mixed cases
comments_incidence: the remaining cases that are for vivax could be also Pm but very unlikely and also maybe mixed?
Intervention1: LLIN distribution (probably first round)
coverage1: 1 net per 2.5 for the whole village
implementation_dates_exact_comment: yes there is a graph that says when things are done
baselin_intervention: spraying happening up until the LLINs were introduced,they changed to ACT in january 2010, spraying already before
standard_of_care: pf: used to be chloroquine and shift to artesunate plus sulfadoxine-pyrimethamine, Pv: chlorquine plus primaquine (doesnt say about dose)
transmission: give EIR for the sundargarh district: for An. Fluviatilis which is major vector 0.23-0.39 infective bites per person per day in high trasnmission season, for An. Culicifacies only 0.01
cluster_trial_concern: no just one village
cluster_trial_addressed: not necessary

study_title: Field evaluation of zero vector durable lining to assess ist efficacy against malaria vectors and malaria transmission in tribal areas of the balaghat distrrict of central india
incidence_definition: fever surveys every month: fever or fever in last 14 days and positive smear
comments_incidence: sample sizte is number of people in village… not sure if they went to all door by door
Intervention1: IRS (as spraying done by government could be that not first time, one in july 13 and sept 13)
baselin_intervention: none found
standard_of_care: Pf: northeastern states: AL three days and one dose PQ, oter states: SP and one dose PQ, Pv: Cq three days and PQ for 14 days 0.25 mg per kg per day. If mixed same but no CQ. (according to NVBDCP: diagnosis and treatment of malaria 2013)
cluster_trial_concern: yes, several (8) control villages
cluster_trial_addressed: no, or not mentioned, but don't have CI anyways
study_type: trial but we look at control

study_title: Transmission and control of vivax malaria in Afghan refugee settlements in Pakistan
incidence_definition: records from basic health unit, passive case detection
comments_incidence: web plot digitizer, could also have for different villages but will not be monthly incidence but more yearly
Intervention1: spraying (malathion or lambdacyhalothrin) (probably first time, but very unsure)
baselin_intervention: not sure if spraying happened before, or if what they say in introduction is about the experiment, i think there was no spraying before
standard_of_care: treated with chloroquine in this study when positive, over three days, 25mg per kg
cluster_trial_concern: yes, several villages
cluster_trial_addressed: no, but no CI anway

study_title: Efficacy of topical mosquito repellent (picaridin) plus long-lasting insecticidal nets versus long-lasting insecticidal nets alone for control of malaria: a cluster randomised controlled trial
pr_what_done_mixed: doesn't say, probably counted towards both, in table 2 P spp is less than if you add up Pv and Pf
Intervention1: LLIN (not first distribution, 1 net per individual)
implementation_dates_exact_comment: we know it needs to be between pre trial and the first survey
baselin_intervention: they had nets before as well with pretty high coverage, also promoted the nets a lot
standard_of_care: Pf: AS and MQ, for vivax additionally PQ for 14 days (guidelines from country-profiles WHO)
cluster_trial_concern: yes
cluster_trial_addressed: yes
study_type: trial but we look at control

study_title: Effect of generalised access to early diagnosis and treatment and targeted mass drug administration on Plasmodium falciparum malaria in Eastern Myanmar: an observational study of a regional elimination programme
incidence_definition: cases detected at malaria posts
sample_size_incidence_number_people: not clear, this is a mixture of all the hotspots that got MDA, there are different follow up times. So the closer to time point zero the bigger the population size and at the end tehre will be less because not all have such a long follow up. In total 12465 people in hotspot village
Intervention1: MDA (3 times a month apart, dihydroartemisnin (7mg per kg) and piperaquine (55mg per kg), 3 days once per day, probably first time apart from maybe pilot
implementation_dates_exact_comment: kinda, know how long it took to implement, but on different dates for different areas, but given with time point 0 being when they started with implementation
baselin_intervention: also increased early diagnosis, also could get LLINs if they needed
standard_of_care: Pf: artemether-lumefantrine, twice per day for three days a single dose primaquine, Pv: chloroquine
cluster_trial_concern: yes, several hotspots where they did MDA
cluster_trial_addressed: not for CI of incidence rates, did account for it to model effect

sample_size_incidence_number_people: not clear, this is a mixture of all the hotspots that got MDA, there are different follow up times. So the closer to time point zero the bigger the population size and at the end tehre will be less because not all have such a long follow up. In total 12465 people in hotspot village
Intervention1: MDA (3 times a month apart, dihydroartemisnin (7mg per kg) and piperaquine (55mg per kg), 3 days once per day, probably first time apart from maybe pilot
implementation_dates_exact_comment: kinda, know how long it took to implement, but on different dates for different areas, but given with time point 0 being when they started with implementation
baselin_intervention: also increased early diagnosis, also could get LLINs if they needed
standard_of_care: Pf: artemether-lumefantrine, twice per day for three days a single dose primaquine, Pv: chloroquine
cluster_trial_concern: yes, several hotspots where they did MDA
cluster_trial_addressed: not for CI of incidence rates, did account for it to model effect

study_title: Pyrethroid-impregnated bed nets for personal protection against malaria for Afghan refugees
incidence_definition: cases detected at health centers
comments_incidence: t in 1991 with some that dont have net. So not community effects but more individual, later some mor people in village got net. Could have a bit of community effect then
Intervention1: control to ITN (permethrin treated)
Intervention2: control to starting of anual retreating
implementation_dates_exact_comment: exact for bednets but reimpregnation only know that inapril for 1992 and spraying assume to be around july because that is when they did it in 1994
baselin_intervention: spraying was taken up during the study (1992/93/94)but in both contorl and  not control
standard_of_care: Pf: 3 days chloroquine with 25mg per kg, Pv: chlrooquine and 5 days primaquine with 1.25mg per kg
cluster_trial_concern: yes, two villages
cluster_trial_addressed: no, but dont have CI
study_type: RCT in 1996, then follow up more observational

study_title: Malaria control using indoor residual spraying and larvivorous fish: a case study in Betul, central India
incidence_definition: cases of fever or history of fever with positive blood slide
Intervention1: increased case management
Intervention2: IRS (pyrtehroid, repeated, before they used DDT, so there was spraying the year before)
implementation_dates_exact_comment: no, just know what year it was done in
baselin_intervention: spraying already happened in year before but with DDT, also added some fish
standard_of_care: Pf. Sulfadoxine-pyrimethamine 1500mg, 1 dose, and primaquine 1 dose 45mg Pv: CQ for 3 days and PQ 75mg for 5 days
cluster_trial_concern: yes, several villages and PHC
cluster_trial_addressed: no, but no CI anyways

Intervention1: LLIN 1st dist
Intervention2: LLIN 2nd dist
implementation_dates_exact_comment: N, LLIN 1st round in 2008, test and treat end of 2011 beginning of 2012
baselin_intervention: no spraying mentioned, had nets before. Coverage around 88% but most likely untreated nets
standard_of_care: before switch (according to omekaius): AL or amodiaquine and SP, end 2011 beginnning of 2012 switch to AL as first line and primaquine for vivax: for 14 days 0.25mg/kg
cluster_trial_concern: no, seperate data for villages
cluster_trial_addressed: not necessary

baselin_intervention: had mainly early diagnosis and treatment

study_area: Pakistan, Mardan district, Baghicha and Kagan
study_title: Pyrethroid-impregnated bed nets for personal protection against malaria for Afghan refugees
Intervention1: control to ITN (permethrin treated)
Intervention2: control to starting of anual retreating
implementation_dates_exact_comment: exact for bednets but reimpregnation only know that inapril for 1992 and spraying assume to be around july because that is when they did it in 1994
baselin_intervention: spraying was taken up during the study (1992/93/94)but in both contorl and  not control
standard_of_care: Pf: 3 days chloroquine with 25mg per kg, Pv: chlrooquine and 5 days primaquine with 1.25mg per kg
cluster_trial_concern: yes, two villages
cluster_trial_addressed: no, but dont have CI
study_type: RCT in 1996, then follow up more observational
